OL,6,FThe court heard Hill then went back to
OL,7,Fher client's home with the aim of
OL,8,F"removing her" as a witness to the
OL,9,Ftheft.
OL,11,FLetting herself in with a key from the
OL,12,Fkey safe Hill hit Mrs Thompson over
OL,13,Fthe head and, as the pensioner fought
OL,14,Fback and began shouting, she then
OL,15,Fsuffocated her.
OL,17,FJudge Meany added: "The suddenness,
OL,18,Fferocity and persistence of the
OL,19,Fviolence you used demonstrates I am
OL,20,Fsure that you went there that night
OL,21,Fintending to kill your victim.
