OL,4,Cold and stole #60 from her purse
OL,6,F"Myra had worked in a caring role all
OL,7,Fher life in Clatterbridge Cancer Unit,
OL,8,Fas well as caring for her disabled
OL,9,Fhusband for 50 years.
OL,11,F"Myra was a trusting, kind, loyal and
OL,12,Fintelligent lady who never hurt
OL,13,Fanyone. Ever.
OL,15,F"All Myra wanted and deserved was to
OL,16,Fspend the rest of her days in the
OL,17,Fcomfort of her own home and be treated
OL,18,Fwith the respect and dignity she has
OL,19,Fshown to others."
